PN,42203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1776255072
OL,3,CScientists confirm fireball seen in
OL,4,Cnight skies was meteor
OL,6,FHe also said it was travelling at a
OL,7,Fspeed of 8.3km per second, and that it
OL,8,Fburned up over the North Sea.
OL,10,FThe dazzling display was also captured
OL,11,Fon camera by Peter McConnell in
OL,12,FThornaby and Zak Flooring in
OL,13,FScarborough
OL,15,FMeanwhile, the UK Fireball Alliance
OL,16,Fsaid they received reports of the
OL,17,Fmeteor from far and wide.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/5
