PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1776255072
OL,3,CScientists confirm fireball seen in
OL,4,Cnight skies was meteor
OL,6,FThe organisation's secretary, Dr
OL,7,FCharlotte Bays, said: "UKFAll received
OL,8,Fclose to 200 eye-witness reports from
OL,9,Fthe general public in the UK and
OL,10,Facross much of northwestern Europe.
OL,12,F"The colour of the fireball largely
OL,13,Freflects the ionized chemical elements
OL,14,Freleased as a meteor travels through
OL,15,Fthe Earth's atmosphere - in this case,
OL,16,Fthe blue-green colour likely reflects
OL,17,Fthe magnesium or perhaps nickel
OL,18,Fcontent.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/5
